---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Weyland-Yutani Corporation Privacy Policy governing the collection, use, and protection of personal data across Earth-based and off-world operations."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="bg-black pt-36">
    <!-- HEADER -->
    <section class="relative py-20 border-b-4 border-[#FFC600] overflow-hidden">
      <div class="industrial-grid absolute inset-0 opacity-10"></div>

      <div class="relative container mx-auto px-6 text-center py-12">
        <span class="text-[#FFC600] text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em] font-mono">LEGAL</span>
        <h1 class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-black text-white leading-none uppercase mt-4 mb-6">
          PRIVACY <span class="text-[#FFC600]">POLICY</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">EFFECTIVE DATE: JANUARY 1, 2120 | LAST UPDATED: MARCH 15, 2120</p>
      </div>

      <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 hazard-stripes h-2"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- POLICY CONTENT -->
    <section class="relative py-16 bg-black">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-8 text-sm">

            <div class="corp-card p-6 mb-10">
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 font-mono leading-relaxed">
                This Privacy Policy ("Policy") describes how Weyland-Yutani Corporation, its subsidiaries, affiliates, and controlled entities (collectively, "Weyland-Yutani," "the Corporation," "we," "us," or "our") collect, use, disclose, and protect personal information in connection with our websites, applications, products, services, and operations across all Earth-based and off-world jurisdictions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">1. SCOPE OF THIS POLICY</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
                This Policy applies to all personal data collected by Weyland-Yutani Corporation through: (a) our corporate websites and digital platforms; (b) products and services provided to consumers, enterprise clients, and governmental entities; (c) employment and recruitment activities; (d) colony administration and resident services; (e) vessel operations and crew management; (f) research participation programs; and (g) any other interaction with the Corporation or its representatives.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                This Policy applies across all jurisdictions in which the Corporation operates, including but not limited to terrestrial nations, lunar installations, orbital platforms, and off-world colony administrations. Where local law imposes requirements that exceed this Policy, the Corporation will comply with the more protective standard.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">Weyland-Yutani collects the following categories of personal information:</p>

              <h3 class="text-base font-black text-white uppercase mt-6 mb-2">2.1 IDENTITY AND CONTACT INFORMATION</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Name, date of birth, nationality, government-issued identification numbers, biometric identifiers (fingerprint, retinal scan, voiceprint), postal and electronic addresses, communications relay identifiers, and colony registration numbers.</p>

              <h3 class="text-base font-black text-white uppercase mt-6 mb-2">2.2 EMPLOYMENT AND PROFESSIONAL DATA</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Employment history, educational credentials, professional certifications, security clearance level, vessel assignment records, colony posting history, performance evaluations, and compensation data.</p>

              <h3 class="text-base font-black text-white uppercase mt-6 mb-2">2.3 HEALTH AND BIOMETRIC DATA</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Medical records generated through MedPod systems, hypersleep physiological data, deep-space radiation exposure records, fitness-for-duty assessments, and genetic screening results where required by operational safety regulations.</p>

              <h3 class="text-base font-black text-white uppercase mt-6 mb-2">2.4 TECHNICAL AND USAGE DATA</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Device identifiers, IP addresses, browser and operating system information, access logs, navigation patterns on Corporation digital platforms, and communications metadata transmitted through Corporation networks.</p>

              <h3 class="text-base font-black text-white uppercase mt-6 mb-2">2.5 LOCATION DATA</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">GPS coordinates, vessel tracking data, colony zone access logs, facility entry and exit records, and interstellar transit manifests.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">The Corporation uses personal information for the following purposes:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Provision and improvement of products, services, and operational systems</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Employee and crew management, including assignment, compensation, and performance evaluation</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Colony administration and resident service delivery</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Safety, security, and emergency response across all installations</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and contractual obligations</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Research and development, including anonymized data analysis</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> Communications, marketing, and corporate relationship management</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">4. SYNTHETIC PERSON DATA PROCESSING</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
                Weyland-Yutani synthetic persons generate and process operational data in the course of their assigned duties. This data, including cognitive logs, behavioral analytics, and interaction records, is the property of Weyland-Yutani Corporation and is subject to the Corporation's data governance framework. Synthetic operational data is not classified as personal data under this Policy.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                Personal data of human individuals collected or processed by synthetic persons in the course of their duties is subject to the full protections of this Policy. Synthetic persons are programmed to adhere to all data handling protocols established by the Corporation.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">5. INTERSTELLAR DATA TRANSFERS</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
                The Corporation operates across multiple star systems and routinely transfers data between Earth-based facilities, orbital platforms, and off-world installations via FTL communications relay and conventional data transport. All interstellar data transfers are encrypted using Corporation-standard quantum-resistant encryption protocols.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                Where data is transferred between jurisdictions with differing data protection standards, the Corporation applies the higher standard of protection. Colony administrations operating under the Interstellar Commerce Commission framework are subject to the ICC Data Protection Directive, with which the Corporation maintains full compliance.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">6. DATA RETENTION</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                Personal data is retained for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Policy, subject to applicable legal retention requirements. Employment records are retained for the duration of employment plus 25 years. Colony resident records are retained for the duration of residency plus 15 years. Health records generated by MedPod systems are retained indefinitely for medical continuity purposes unless deletion is specifically requested and legally permissible.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">7. YOUR RIGHTS</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
                Subject to applicable law, you may exercise the following rights with respect to your personal data:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> <strong class="text-white">Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> <strong class="text-white">Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> <strong class="text-white">Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your data where retention is no longer necessary</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> <strong class="text-white">Portability:</strong> Request transfer of your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
                <li class="text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-[#FFC600] mt-1 text-xs">&#9632;</span> <strong class="text-white">Objection:</strong> Object to processing of your data for certain purposes</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mt-3">
                Rights requests may be submitted to privacy@weylandyutani.com or through the Corporation's Data Rights Portal. Requests will be processed within 30 standard Earth days, or 45 days for requests originating from off-world installations.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">8. SECURITY</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                Weyland-Yutani employs administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect personal data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include quantum-resistant encryption, multi-factor biometric authentication, network segmentation, continuous monitoring, and regular security audits conducted by independent third parties.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mb-4">9. CONTACT</h2>
              <div class="h-px w-16 bg-[#FFC600] mb-4"></div>
              <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
                For questions regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact:
              </p>
              <div class="mt-4 p-6 bg-[#0a0a0a] border border-[#1a1a1a] clip-corner">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
                  <strong class="text-white">Office of the Chief Privacy Officer</strong><br/>
                  Weyland-Yutani Corporation<br/>
                  One Weyland Plaza, San Francisco, CA 94111<br/>
                  privacy@weylandyutani.com<br/>
                  +1-800-555-WYPR
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[#1a1a1a]">
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-mono leading-relaxed">
                WEYLAND-YUTANI CORPORATION RESERVES THE RIGHT TO MODIFY THIS PRIVACY POLICY AT ANY TIME. MATERIAL CHANGES WILL BE COMMUNICATED THROUGH CORPORATE DIGITAL PLATFORMS AND, WHERE REQUIRED, THROUGH DIRECT NOTIFICATION. CONTINUED USE OF CORPORATION SERVICES FOLLOWING PUBLICATION OF CHANGES CONSTITUTES ACCEPTANCE OF THE REVISED POLICY.
              </p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .clip-corner {
    clip-path: polygon(8px 0, 100% 0, 100% calc(100% - 8px), calc(100% - 8px) 100%, 0 100%, 0 8px);
  }
</style>
